==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foggy
<hw>Fog"gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Foggier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Foggiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[From 4th <er>Fog</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Filled or abounding with fog, or watery exhalations;
misty; <as>as, a <ex>foggy</ex> atmosphere; a <ex>foggy</ex>
morning.</as></def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 578 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Beclouded; dull; obscure; <as>as, <ex>foggy</ex>
ideas</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your coarse, <qex>foggy</qex>, drowsy conceit.</q>
<rj><qau>Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>foghorn</ent>⟦br⟧
